The paper deals with the task of locating handwritten annotations in historic German documents using Fully Convolutional Neural Networks (FCNN). This task falls under the domain of computer vision and image processing, which is covered by the cs.CV sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and training strategies, which are common topics in machine learning and deep learning, covered by the cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.DL sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the results using the Layout Analysis Evaluator, which is a tool used in natural language processing and document analysis, covered by the cs.CL sub-category.
